The paper deals with learning and synthesizing torque control commands for robots, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The approach proposed involves probabilistic learning, which suggests a connection to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of force constraints also suggests a connection to control systems (cs.SY). Finally, the validation of the approach in experimental scenarios suggests a connection to computer vision (cs.CV) for perception and sensing.
